xpert%3DMario_J._DiFiore%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereleased%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20analysis%20examining%20the%20share%20of%20median%20income%20residents%20of%20US%20states%20allocate%20to%20groceries%2C%20and%20those%20in%20Mississippi%2C%20West%20Virginia%2C%20and%20Arkansas%20are%20spending%20the%20highest%20percentages.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20company%20studied%20the%20prices%20of%2026%20common%20grocery%20items%2C%20including%20meat%2C%20dairy%2C%20fruits%2C%20and%20cleaning%20products%2C%20across%20all%2050%20states.%20It%20then%20combined%20the%20costs%20and%20compared%20them%20with%20the%20median%20household%20income%20in%20each%20state%20to%20identify%20where%20residents%20spend%20the%20highest%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmillennials-gen-z-splurge-groceries-spending-inflation-gen-z-boomers-2024-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproportion%20of%20their%20income%20on%20groceries%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMississippi%20ranked%20No.%201%20on%20the%20list%20for%20highest%20spending%20on%20groceries%20relative%20to%20income%2C%20with%20the%20cost%20of%20groceries%20reaching%202.64%25%20of%20median%20monthly%20household%20income.%20West%20Virginia%20ranked%20No.%202%20with%202.57%25%2C%20and%20Arkansas%20ranked%20No.%203%20with%202.49%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYou%20can%20hover%20over%20the%20map%20below%20to%20see%20the%20percentage%20of%20median%20monthly%20household%20income%20residents%20spend%20on%20groceries%20by%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FRVOwO%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Cost%20of%20groceries%20as%20a%20share%20of%20median%20monthly%20household%20income%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22528%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20Mississippi%20ranking%20highest%20on%20the%20list%2C%20the%20report%20said%20that%20%26quot%3Bgrocery%20prices%20in%20Mississippi%20are%20actually%20relatively%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20with%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethe%20state%20having%20the%20ninth%20lowest%20grocery%20prices%20in%20the%20US.%20WalletHub%20said%20in%20its%20findings%20that%20Mississippi%20is%20among%20the%2010%20least%20expensive%20states%20in%2015%20of%20the%2026%20products%20measured%20in%20the%20study%2C%20including%20items%20like%20margarine%20and%20dishwashing%20detergent.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20a%20more%20significant%20factor%20is%20that%20Mississippi%20had%20the%20lowest%20median%20annual%20household%20income%20in%20the%20country%2C%20at%20%2452%2C985%20in%202022%20dollars%2C%20per%20Census%20data%20spanning%202018%20through%202022.%20That%20was%20well%20below%20the%20national%20median%20of%20%2475%2C149.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%20even%20with%20relatively%20low%20grocery%20prices%20overall%2C%20Mississippians%20are%20spending%20a%20higher%20percentage%20of%20their%20income%20on%20groceries%20than%20people%20in%20any%20other%20state%2C%26quot%3B%20WalletHub%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWalletHub%20analyst%20Chip%20Lupo%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20the%20study%20compared%20the%20prices%20in%20each%20state%20to%20median%20annual%20income%20because%20it%20seemed%20to%20be%20a%20better%20indicator%20on%20a%20statewide%20basis%20than%20solely%20looking%20at%20grocery%20prices.%20Lupo%20said%20that%20the%20cost%20of%20grocery%20prices%20in%20New%20Jersey%20%26quot%3Bwon't%20mean%20anything%20to%20someone%20in%20West%20Virginia.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20West%20Virginia%20is%20%26quot%3Baround%20the%20middle%20or%20bottom%20of%20the%20country%26quot%3B%20for%20some%20of%20its%20grocery%20prices%2C%20although%20some%20products%2C%20like%20eggs%20and%20potatoes%2C%20tend%20to%20be%20more%20expensive.%20Still%2C%20West%20Virginia%20had%20the%20second-lowest%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-costs-for-our-family-six-enormous-how-we-save-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emedian%20household%20income%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20US%2C%20bringing%20in%20%2455%2C217%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20while%20Arkansas%2C%20which%20spends%20the%20third-highest%20percentage%20of%20its%20median%20income%20on%20groceries%2C%20is%20in%20the%20top%2010%20states%20with%20the%20cheapest%20groceries%20in%20the%20US%2C%20it%20has%20the%20third-lowest%20median%20household%20income%2C%20with%20%2456%2C335%20annually.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20New%20Jersey%20ranked%20No.%2050%20on%20the%20list%2C%20meaning%20its%20residents%20spend%20the%20lowest%20percentage%20of%20their%20income%20on%20groceries%2C%20with%20Maryland%20and%20Massachusetts%20placing%20right%20above%20it.%20All%20three%20states%20have%20the%20highest%20median%20annual%20household%20incomes%20in%20the%20country%20and%20spend%20between%201.5%25%20and%201.54%25%20of%20their%20median%20monthly%20household%20income%20on%20groceries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELupo%20suggested%20that%20those%20who%20want%20to%20see%20their%20spending%20go%20down%20should%20buy%20store-brand%20versions%20of%20products%2C%20buy%20in%20bulk%2C%20and%20look%20into%20reward%20programs%20for%20grocery%20stores%20they%20frequent.%20You%20should%20also%20budget%20carefully%20%E2%80%94%20and%20try%20to%20stick%20to%20it%2C%20Lupo%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20will%20keep%20you%20from%20splurging%2C%26quot%3B%20Lupo%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20most%20importantly%2C%20from%20making%20those%20impulse%20buys.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-prices-spending-map-us-states-compared-income-mississippi-highest-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740502068000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bc8374c832c3638fa500da%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-prices-spending-map-us-states-compared-income-mississippi-highest-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20recent%20WalletHub%20analysis%20compared%20the%20prices%20of%2026%20common%20grocery%20items%20with%20the%20median%20household%20income%20in%20each%20state.%20Mississippi%20ranked%20No.%201.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22aaltchek%40insider.com%20(Ana%20Altchek%2CMadison%20Hoff)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgrocery-prices-spending-map-us-states-compared-income-mississippi-highest-2025-2%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22After%20Meeting%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20France's%20Macron%20Reveals%20The%20Endgame%20In%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20an%20hours-long%20meeting%20with%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20Washington%20DC%2C%20French%20President%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20laid%20down%20the%20endgame%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20suggesting%20that%20a%20peace%20deal%20or%20ceasefire%20agreement%20is%20highly%20likely%20in%20a%20matter%20of%20weeks.%20He%20also%20spoke%20in%20detail%20about%20his%20meeting%20with%20President%20Trump%20and%20what%20the%20outcomes%20from%20that%20meeting%20will%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPresident%20Macron%20was%20representing%20all%20of%20Europe%20at%20today's%20meeting%20with%20President%20Trump%2C%20since%20Europe%20share%20a%20common%20concern%20over%20security.%20Mr%20Macron%20had%20held%20a%20meeting%20with%20top%20leaders%20of%20the%20European%20Union%20last%20week.%20They%20had%20held%20a%20meeting%20in%20Paris%20over%20concerns%20that%20a%20US-Russia%20direct%20deal%20on%20Ukraine%20will%20not%20take%20into%20account%20Ukraine%20and%20Europe's%20concerns%20on%20security.%20They%20echoed%20the%20same%20sentiment%20-%20that%20talks%20on%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20cannot%20happen%20without%20Ukraine%20and%20Europe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ETHE%20ENDGAME%20SEQUENCE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDonald%20Trump%20has%20said%20that%20the%20three-year-long%20Ukraine%20war%20will%20end%20within%20weeks%2C%20and%20President%20Trump%20shared%20his%20optimism.%20Calling%20the%20arrival%20of%20President%20Trump%20to%20negotiations%20on%20Ukraine%20as%20a%20%26quot%3Bgame-changer%26quot%3B%2C%20the%20French%20President%20said%20%26quot%3Bhe%20knows%20how%20to%20re-engage%20with%20Russia%20with%20the%20full%20deterrence%20capacity%20of%20the%20US%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMr%20Macron%20however%20cautioned%20the%20US%20President%20not%20to%20rush%20into%20a%20deal%20with%20Moscow.%20%26quot%3BIn%202014%2C%20we%20had%20a%20peace%20deal%20with%20Russia.%20I%20can%20tell%20you%20from%20personal%20experience%2C%20since%20I%20was%20one%20of%20the%20two%20members%20along%20with%20German%20representative%20to%20follow%20up%20on%20the%20ceasefire.%20Russia%20grossly%20violated%20every%20single%20time%20-%20and%20none%20of%20us%20reacted%20collectively.%20So%20the%20issue%20is%20of%20trust%20and%20credibility%20-%20how%20to%20ensure%20Russia%20does%20not%20do%20this%20again%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%20in%20an%20interview%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22No%20follow%2C%20no%20index%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.foxnews.com%2Fvideo%2F6369277034112%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFox%20News%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20say%20that%20%26quot%3BFor%20me%20the%20sequence%20of%20the%20ceasefire%20agreement%20should%20be%20as%20follows%20-%20First%20there%20should%20be%20a%20negotiation%20between%20the%20US%20and%20Russia%20and%20then%20the%20US%20and%20Ukraine.%20President%20Trump%20has%20announced%20today%20that%20he%20is%20willing%20to%20have%20a%20short-term%20meeting%20with%20Ukraine's%20President%20Zelensky%20-%20this%20is%20super%20important.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20truce%20could%20actually%20happen%20in%20the%20weeks%20to%20come%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20%26quot%3BTruce%20has%20to%20be%20achieved%20on%20land%2C%20in%20the%20air%2C%20and%20at%20sea%2C%20and%20infrastructure%20(installed%20in%20Ukraine)%20-%20and%20Russia%20must%20respect%20it.%20If%20it%20doesn't%20it%20will%20be%20clear%20that%20Moscow%20is%20not%20serious%20about%20a%20peace%20deal%26quot%3B%20and%20Ukraine's%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-media-max-width%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EOn%20Fox%20News%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ft.co%2F1dBUFDEOYW%5C%22%3Epic.twitter.com%2F1dBUFDEOYW%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%E2%80%94%20Emmanuel%20Macron%20(%40EmmanuelMacron)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FEmmanuelMacron%2Fstatus%2F1894367003516801292%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EFebruary%2025%2C%202025%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDuring%20this%20period%20of%20time%20-%20when%20the%20truce%20is%20in%20place%2C%20we%20negotiate%20-%20on%20security%20guarantees%20(by%20Moscow)%2C%20on%20land%20and%20territories%20(to%20reclaim%20or%20surrender)%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20Ukrainian%20President%20(to%20safeguard%20Kyiv's%20interest)%2C%26quot%3B%20President%20Macron%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said%2C%20Washington%20%26quot%3Bwill%20secure%20a%20deal%20on%20rare%20earth%20and%20other%20critical%20minerals%26quot%3B.%20Confirming%20that%20France%20and%20the%20rest%20of%20Europe%20will%20be%20fine%20with%20this%2C%20Mr%20Macron%20explained%20that%20such%20a%20mineral%20deal%20for%20Washington%20%26quot%3Bis%20important%2C%20because%20this%20would%20be%20the%20best%20way%20to%20guarantee%20that%20the%20US%20is%20also%20committed%26quot%3B%20and%20not%20back%20out%20of%20Ukraine's%20safety%20and%20sovereignty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20on%20the%20back%20of%20this%20set%20of%20manoeuvres%2C%20with%20all%20parties%20invested%20in%20maintaining%20Ukraine's%20sovereignty%2C%20we%20will%20finally%20have%20a%20peace%20deal%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EKEY%20STEPS%20AFTER%20THE%20PEACE%20DEAL%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHow%20can%20one%20guarantee%20that%20Russia%20will%20not%20violate%20this%20treaty%20in%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20French%20President%20questioned%20before%20giving%20the%20answer%20himself.%20%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20consensus%20for%20NATO%2C%20or%20having%20Ukraine%20join%20NATO%2C%20but%20if%20we%20(European%20NATO%20members)%20leave%20Ukraine%20alone%2C%20like%20we%20did%20in%20the%20past%2C%26quot%3B%20there%20is%20a%20risk%20for%20another%20invasion%20by%20Russia%2C%20he%20explained.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20as%20a%20follow-up%20to%20the%20ceasefire%2C%20we%20need%20to%20see%20which%20type%20of%20security%20guarantee%20we%20need%20going%20forward.%20One%20can%20be%20to%20increase%20the%20capacity%20of%20Ukraine%20to%20maintain%20a%20very%20strong%20army%20(on%20the%20Russian%20front).%20The%20second%20option%20will%20be%20for%20France%20and%20the%20UK%20to%20work%20together%20on%20a%20proposal%20that%20the%20two%20nations%20will%20send%20combined%20troops%20to%20Ukraine%20-%20not%20to%20go%20to%20the%20frontline%2C%20not%20to%20go%20on%20confrontation%2C%20but%20to%20be%20stationed%20at%20locations%20agreed%20upon%20by%20the%20treaty%20that%20all%20parties%20agree%20on.%20The%20aim%20will%20be%20just%20to%20maintain%20a%20troops%20presence%20in%20Ukraine%20to%20keep%20a%20check%20on%20Russia's%20credibility.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20will%20be%20with%20the%20backing%20of%20the%20US%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Europe's%20responsibility%20and%20the%20sharing%20of%20costs%2C%20which%20President%20Trump%20has%20said%20is%20%26quot%3Babsent%26quot%3B%2C%20President%20Macron%20said%20%26quot%3BWe%20(Europe)%20are%20ready%20to%20take%20our%20fair%20share%20of%20the%20burden%2C%20since%20it%20is%20in%20Europe.%20I%20have%20already%20spoken%20with%20around%2