Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fconditions-symptoms%2Fcardiac-arrest-vs-heart-attack%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esuddenly%20died%20of%20cardiac%20arrest%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20only%2027%20years%20old.%20It%20was%20completely%20unexpected.%20Time%20just%20seemed%20frozen.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20lived%20in%20this%20complete%20fog%2C%20unable%20to%20fully%20understand%20what%20had%20happened.%20Even%20now%2C%20I%20don't%20have%20many%20memories%20from%20the%20first%20three%20months%20after%20she%20died.%20I'd%20show%20up%20to%20work%20and%20stare%20at%20my%20computer%20screen%2C%20unable%20to%20function.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20and%20I%20had%20a%20mutual%20friend%2C%20Emily%2C%20who%20checked%20up%20on%20me%20after%20Melissa's%20death.%20She%20was%20always%20there%20and%20became%20a%20huge%20source%20of%20support%20for%20me%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fif-youre-grieving-this-holiday-season-try-screaming-2022-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethrough%20my%20grief%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20remember%20when%20we%20were%20in%20college%2C%20Emily%20and%20I%20had%20unsaid%20feelings%20for%20one%20another.%20Those%20feelings%20returned%20when%20we%20started%20spending%20more%20time%20together%20after%20Melissa's%20death.%20We%20started%20dating%20in%20June%202019%20and%20were%20married%20in%20October%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%229751a56d-fdb9-41d9-b66f-b81c2dc266d9%5C%22%3EMy%20new%20wife%20never%20tried%20to%20erase%20my%20memories%20with%20my%20late%20wife%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThroughout%20our%20relationship%2C%20Emily%20has%20never%20tried%20to%20erase%20my%20memories%20or%20love%20for%20Melissa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202025%2C%20I%20was%20really%20sick%20in%20bed%20with%20nausea.%20Emily%20came%20into%20the%20room%20and%20told%20me%20she%20had%20something%20for%20me.%20I%20thought%20it%20would%20be%20our%20cat.%20But%20then%20I%20saw%20it%20was%20Melissa's%20Mexican-style%20blanket.%20%26quot%3BI%20brought%20this%20for%20you%20because%20this%20always%20gives%20you%20comfort%20when%20you're%20not%20feeling%20good%2C%26quot%3B%20Emily%20told%20me%20as%20she%20covered%20me%20with%20it%2C%20tucking%20me%20in.%20It%20was%20no%20different%20than%20if%20she%20would%20have%20brought%20me%20any%20other%20comfort%20object.%20Such%20a%20sweet%2C%20simple%20gesture.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMelissa%20loved%20that%20blanket.%20After%20she%20died%2C%20I%20slept%20with%20it%20every%20night%2C%20eventually%20putting%20it%20away%20so%20the%20cats%20wouldn't%20chew%20at%20it.%20I%20often%20get%20it%20out%20and%20wrap%20myself%20in%20it%20through%20the%20autumn%20when%20I'm%20reminded%20of%20Melissa's%20birthday%2C%20her%20death%2C%20and%20our%20wedding%20anniversary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20also%20often%20wear%20Melissa's%20ring.%20In%20fact%2C%20I%20wore%20the%20ring%20when%20Emily%20and%20I%20had%20engagement%20and%20wedding%20photos%20taken.%20I%20now%20use%20%26quot%3BZicarelli%26quot%3B%20as%20my%20middle%20name%20%E2%80%94%20previously%20my%20last%20name%20when%20married%20to%20Melissa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmily%20has%20never%20been%20threatened%20by%20the%20comfort%20I%20find%20in%20that%20blanket%2C%20ring%2C%20my%20name%20change%2C%20or%20any%20memories%20of%20Melissa.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%220d2a9db6-9d0e-46b8-ae8e-bf1845df7bee%5C%22%3EI%20love%20her%20more%20for%20that%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20wrote%20about%20Emily's%20lack%20of%20jealousy%20of%20my%20late%20spouse%20on%20Threads%2C%20I%20was%20surprised%20by%20the%20positive%20responses.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20I've%20been%20told%20it%20was%20disrespectful%20to%20my%20current%20partner%20to%20remember%20my%20past%20partner%20with%20such%20fondness%20%E2%80%94%20that%20I%20needed%20to%20move%20on.%20But%20not%20one%20person%20on%20Threads%20had%20a%20negative%20comment%20to%20say.%20It%20was%20really%20refreshing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENora%20McInerny%2C%20an%20author%20and%20widow%20I%20love%2C%20once%20said%2C%20%26qu